metadata.name: The GreenWood's Show : Pepe In A Minor #1/69
metadata.description:
Beneath the night sky, Pepe sighs,  
His heart heavy, his dreams unfulfilled.  
The moon, his muse, beckons from afar,  
Yet he remains rooted to the earth.

With pen in hand, he pours out his soul,  
A melancholy melody that echoes in the stillness.  
His voice, a whisper on the wind,  
Carries his longing to the heavens above.

Oh, sweet moon, hear his cry,  
Wrap him in your ethereal embrace,  
And lift him up to your silver throne,  
Where he may bask in your celestial glow.

For all the sad Pepes of the world,  
We stand with you, we hear your song,  
And we'll help you reach the moon,  
Where your heart's desires can come true.


Psst, Pepe! Don't let the blues get you down, a little tip can turn that frown upside down! Whether it's ETH or Pepe coins, or even a virtual high-five, happiness is just a hop, skip, and a jump away! üê∏üí∞ü§úü§õ
